NAME
pomodoro [-s [profile]] [-k] [-g]

A pomodoro timer manager with a dmenu front end.

SYNOPSIS
arguments

-s, start, if profile name is omitted, dmenu will be open for the selection.

-k, kill, stops the current timer.

-g, get, Gets the timer status.

DESCRIPTION
This command uses the ~/.config/pomodoro/config file to determine timer lengths
and the next timer to move to after the timer is done. When get is run, the 
timer status will be updated in that file.

EXAMPLES
pomodoro -s work

Starts the work timer.

